2 SENATE BILL 77
1 (A) A COUNTY OR MUNICIPALITY, INCLUDING A UNIT OF A COUNTY OR
2 MUNICIPALITY, MAY NOT USE PUBLIC FUNDS TO PROVIDE FUNDING FOR OR
3 PAYMENT TO THE CONSTITUTIONAL SHERIFFS AND PEACE OFFICERS
4 ASSOCIATION, INCLUDING FUNDING OR PAYMENT FOR MEMBERSHIP DUES,
5 TRAININGS, CERTIFICATIONS, OR CONFERENCES.
6 (B) AN ORGANIZATION THAT RECEIVES PUBLIC FUNDS FROM A COUNTY OR
7 MUNICIPALITY MAY NOT USE THOSE FUNDS TO PROVIDE FUNDING FOR OR PAYMENT
8 TO THE CONSTITUTIONAL SHERIFFS AND PEACE OFFICERS ASSOCIATION,
9 INCLUDING FUNDING OR PAYMENT FOR MEMBERSHIP DUES, TRAININGS,
10 CERTIFICATIONS, OR CONFERENCES.
11 Article – State Finance and Procurement
12 7–240.
13 (A) AN OFFICER OR A UNIT OF STATE GOVERNMENT MAY NOT USE ANY PART
14 OF AN APPROPRIATION TO PROVIDE FUNDING FOR OR PAYMENT TO THE
15 CONSTITUTIONAL SHERIFFS AND PEACE OFFICERS ASSOCIATION, INCLUDING
16 FUNDING OR PAYMENT FOR MEMBERSHIP DUES, TRAININGS, CERTIFICATIONS, OR
17 CONFERENCES.
18 (B) AN ORGANIZATION THAT RECEIVES FUNDS APPROPRIATED BY THE
19 STATE MAY NOT USE THOSE FUNDS TO PROVIDE FUNDING FOR OR PAYMENT TO THE
20 CONSTITUTIONAL SHERIFFS AND PEACE OFFICERS ASSOCIATION, INCLUDING
21 FUNDING OR PAYMENT FOR MEMBERSHIP DUES, TRAININGS, CERTIFICATIONS, OR
22 CONFERENCES.
23 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
24 1, 2025.

